# Pagination Default: 10

## Rule

- Default `pageSize` / `limit` = **10** on every paginated list
- User preference may override via saved filters — initial default still 10
- Server and client params must stay in sync (`page`, `limit` or `pageSize`)

## Pattern

```js
const DEFAULT_PAGE_SIZE = 10;
const [pageSize, setPageSize] = useState(saved?.pageSize || DEFAULT_PAGE_SIZE);
```

## When adding pagination

- [ ] Default 10 in state and API params
- [ ] Page size selector includes 10 as first/default option
- [ ] `navPrefetch` keys use same limit if prefetching page 1

Existing refs: `TodoPage.jsx`, `LeadsPage.jsx`, `FinancePage.jsx`.
